caption: GT Hindu YUVA’s official guide on how you can get involved! ॐ Through our org, you can celebrate Hindu festivals with 1000+ other students on campus, discuss Hindu philosophy, learn Sanskrit, and so much more, all while joining a Hindu student community.

Happy Earth Day! Hindu YUVA has switched over to compostable plates, utensils, and trash bags for our events to promote a sustainable future. Learn how you too can help the Earth! 🌎♻️
Make sandwiches with us for the Sandwich Project, an org that has donated 1M+ sandwiches to date! This is a fun opportunity to give back to your Atlanta community 🥪🙏🏽
Thank you to all the 250+ people who came to our last big event of the year! We hope you enjoyed Tour of Ayodhya and learned more about the Ramayana through all of our exhibits! 🛕✨
Thank you all for coming out to SSA Langar 2024! Thank you to @gthinduyuva for organizing this event with us and helping us make it a success yet again!

DHARMA AWARENESS WEEK is next week— our biggest series of events yet! Mark your calendars and come out to our Tour of Ayodhya, Hanuman Movie Screening, and Langar (a fan favorite every year). 🎥 🍲

Learn about the Ramayana at our Tour of Ayodhya @ Student Center! Connect with this epic by mapping the segments to India, participating in interactive activities, and touring exhibits. You won’t want to miss one of our biggest events yet! 🏹 RSVP LINK IN BIO.
BOARD APPS ARE LIVE ‼️ we’re so excited to open our 2024-2025 applications!! 🥳 Join our board to help plan campus wide cultural events and create lasting friendships! LINK IN BIO 🕉️

This past month, the Hindu YUVA boards of chapters across Georgia, Florida, Alabama, North Carolina, and Tennessee met for a weekend of learning, growing, and bonding. We’re so excited for what the future holds for us! #hindu #hinduyuva #hinduism

Join us this Saturday to interact with representatives from the Consulate General of India and learn about the services CGI has to offer Indian international students! This is a great way to get your questions answered and voice any concerns that you may have in an informal setting. Please note that RSVP is required for entry to the event! LINK IN BIO to RSVP and submit any questions that you want addressed during the event.

Join us this Monday to celebrate Shivaratri with the Hindu Temple of Atlanta! 🛕Don’t miss out on this auspicious occasion! LINK IN BIO TO RSVP! 🌑🙏🏽

Desi Dhamaal— come to our next GBM to play indian after-school outdoor games! Tag someone you want to come out with 🏐🏃🏾‍♂️

Our Sewa community is hosting a blood drive to support those in need! Join us on February 20th to help donate blood for the American Red Cross Blood Drive. Your donation could help make a big difference for our community! 💉

A big thank you to everyone that came out to our January General Body Meetings🫶🏽 We loved seeing you all make new friends, play games, and reconnect with your roots. Come out to our February GBMs to join our community!

🚨🚨LOCATION CHANGE: Minute to Win It is now at EX HALL BUCKHEAD. 

Exciting things in store for you this month! Come out to our February general body meetings (open to everyone) — Hot Takes, Desi Dhamaal, and Minute to Win It — to meet new friends while having a great time! 🌶️
Yesterday marked a significant moment in history for Hindus around the world— the inauguration of the Ram Mandir in Ayodhya! Swipe to learn more about this historical event 🧡🧡
Learn the oldest language in the world for free! Come out to our Sanskrit classes, every Wednesday from 6-7 PM. Join the WhatsApp for up-to-date details 📕
Join our weekly Vedanta Study Circle! Open to anyone interested in learning about Hindu philosophy and teachings 📖🤎

Come celebrate Sankranti with us on Jan 17! 🥳We will have fun competitions with trivia and other activities! Hope to see you there!! 

RSVP at tinyurl.com/HYSankranti24

With the semester starting soon, here’s our general body meetings (open to everyone) for January! ❄️ 

We’ve been receiving a lot of DMs lately in how you all can get involved with Hindu YUVA— we appreciate the love, and we thought the best way you can get started is by meeting one another in a fun setting! Come out to our Intro Night, Board Game Night, and Chai & Chat to meet new friends and join our Hindu community🫶🏽

Diwali fair was a huge success! 🪔 Over 1000 joined us to celebrate Diwali, and we're grateful for the fantastic turnout. Hope you had a splendid time with Diwali-inspired activities and live performances! Check out more event pictures in our bio. 📸🪔🙏

We’re so excited to open up our board applications for Spring 2024! 🥳 Join our team to be a part of the planning for all the exciting cultural events we have next semester, all while creating lasting friendships. If you’re a highly motivated person who loves working in teams and making lots of Hindu friends, our board is perfect for you! LINK IN BIO 🕉
To everyone who made it to this year’s Diwali fair: ✨You just looking like a Wow!✨🪔

Last year, we asked you all what your favorite festival is, and the resounding answer was Diwali (check out our “what’s your favorite festival and why?” reel!). Watch to find out why Georgia Tech students love Diwali so much! 🪔🪔 #hindu #diwali #festival

As Hindu YUVA, we understand that the true essence of Diwali lies in selfless service to our community. This festival of lights is not just about the sparkle of lamps but also about brightening hearts through acts of kindness and compassion. 🪔💫

Join us in spreading joy and happiness by engaging in Sewa activities around Diwali! Our events include donation drop boxes, letter writing, and campus kitchen volunteer shifts! We hope to see you there! 🙏🏽

Our biggest event of the year, DIWALI FAIR, is quickly approaching us! 🪔✨ Here’s some information you might want to know, including our performances, activities, and menu for the night. 

Join us on Tech Green on Tuesday, November 14th for a fair of diwali-inspired games, entertainment, and fun— this is the one event you do NOT want to miss! 

Our fair is FREE for all! Because we had a turnout of 1000+ students last year, we would appreciate any volunteers to help out! RSVP links for the event and/or volunteering is in our bio! 🎟️

Presenting GT Hindu YUVA’s Diwali Fair! Join us to celebrate Diwali and enjoy a night filled with live performances, Diwali-inspired activities and free food! We hope to see you there! RSVP link in bio! 🪔
✨A sneak into our Ganesh Chaturthi’ 23✨ Students came to celebrate by making Ganeshas out of clay, watching beautiful performances, and eating delicious food!
Join us for a beautiful Nadaswaram Concert! The Nadaswaram is an ancient temple instrument that’s rarely heard in public, so this is an exciting listening opportunity. RSVP link in bio :)
Celebrate Navratri with us on Monday, October 16th! We will make a golu and listen to the stories behind this festival ☺️ RSVP IN BIO!
Georgia announced October as Hindu Heritage Month! Read on to learn what this month is and what it celebrates 🕉️
Introducing our new 2023-24 Exec 🤎 We have so many exciting things planned for the year!

Our Ganesh Chaturthi event had an incredible 400-person turnout! We enjoyed making clay Ganeshas, watching beautiful performances, and eating an authentic Indian dinner with everyone. We hope to see you at our next event!

Celebrate MyGanesha, our exclusive Ganesh Chaturthi event! There will be clay Ganesha making, performances, and authentic Indian food. RSVP link in bio ✨
Our Vedanta study circle will be held every Friday at 6:00 to 7:00 pm at Skiles! Please join us to learn about Hindu philosophy and more! Hope to see all of you there!
Hindu YUVA and ICGT are thrilled to host a captivating talk by Amma Sri Karunamayi! This talk will discuss overcoming anxiety and self-doubt. We hope to see you all there! 🙏 RSVP in bio!

Our first HY hangout of the year turned out amazing! We expressed our creative sides by making rakhi’s while also learning about the significance of Raksha Bandhan! We had a great time with everyone that joined us! 🙏

Join Hindu YUVA in a beginners two-day Spoken Sanskrit Workshop!! Learn basic Sanskrit in one weekend in an interactive workshop led by an instructor from Samskrita Bharati! No prior experience is necessary. By the end of the workshop, you will feel comfortable starting a conversation in Sanskrit!! RSVP now using the link in our bio!
